The whole main stream media deal with the revision of the whole socialism issue, about which opinions still differ a lot. And today is exactly the 30th anniversary of the Revolution. Hard to believe it now, but a true revolution as it was followed by the dissolution of the Czechoslovakia in 1992 and the establishment of the two states, the Czech Republic declared by its parliament on the 1st of January, 1993.

HISTORY OF THE CZECH REPUBLIC

The institute of the Czech state in the southwest part of the present day Czech Republic goes back to the 9th century. Between the 10th and 13th centuries the Czech-state area diversified. In the 12th and 13th centuries it was the Hungary dominion. In the 13th and 14th centuries Hungarian king and emperors managed the process of the formation of the state and are considered as the de facto inventors of the Czech state. In the 15th century the two states, Bohemia and Moravia, were united by Czech king and Bohemian king of the Romans elected at the Prague castle and Hungary had breached by the Ottoman Empire as took also Silesia.
